# JESSE's .gitignore for flipper-zero-au-subghz
#
# This repo is for education + your own verified captures on hardware you own.
# Real key fob/gate captures often contain sensitive timing data that some people
# prefer to keep private. This .gitignore helps you avoid accidentally committing
# them to public history.
#
# Adjust to taste. The important bit is: don't commit other people's cars.

# ============================================================================
# REAL CAPTURES — the big one
# ============================================================================
# Any actual .sub files captured from real key fobs or remotes.
# Templates and generated skeletons are fine to keep.
# If you really want to commit your own verified captures (with good metadata),
# you can git add -f them or remove/adjust these lines.

# car_hacks_au brand folders — YOUR captures only live here
car_hacks_au/**/*.sub
car_hacks_au/*.sub

# Any loose captures people might drop in root, playlists, scripts, etc.
*.sub

# But keep the example/template .sub files that the generator produces
!fcc_research/generated/*_template.sub
!templates/**/*.sub

# ============================================================================
# GENERATED / RESEARCH FILES — allowed through the blanket *.sub block above
# ============================================================================
# These are generated template/research files, NOT real fob captures.
# Real captures from your own hardware should be added with: git add -f <file>

# Subaru Forester fixed-code research collection
!car_hacks_au/subaru/forester_fixed/**/*.sub

# ATA gate research files  
!car_hacks_au/gates/ata_gates/**/*.sub

# Brand-specific generated research templates (fixed code, KeeLoq counter sequences)
!car_hacks_au/ford_ranger/**/*.sub
!car_hacks_au/holden_commodore/**/*.sub
!car_hacks_au/honda/**/*.sub
!car_hacks_au/isuzu_dmax/**/*.sub
!car_hacks_au/jeep/**/*.sub
!car_hacks_au/ldv_t60/**/*.sub
!car_hacks_au/mazda/**/*.sub
!car_hacks_au/mazda_bt50/**/*.sub
!car_hacks_au/mitsubishi/**/*.sub
!car_hacks_au/nissan/**/*.sub
!car_hacks_au/suzuki/**/*.sub
!car_hacks_au/vw_amarok/**/*.sub
!car_hacks_au/hyundai_kia/**/*.sub
!car_hacks_au/toyota/**/*.sub
!car_hacks_au/great_wall_cannon/**/*.sub
!car_hacks_au/gates/*.sub

# Keys directory (top fixed codes)
!car_hacks_au/keys/**/*.sub

# FLIPPER_SD_PACKAGE (pre-structured for deployment)
!FLIPPER_SD_PACKAGE/**/*.sub

# Playlists
!playlists/**/*.txt
!FLIPPER_SD_PACKAGE/**/playlists/**/*.txt

# ============================================================================
# Python
# ============================================================================
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
build/
develop-eggs/
dist/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
lib/
lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg

# Virtual environments
.venv/
venv/
ENV/
env/

# ============================================================================
# Testing / temp artefacts from the helper scripts
# ============================================================================
scripts/test_*/
scripts/test_*.sub
scripts/test_*.txt
rolljam_prep_notes_*.txt
*.tmp
*.temp

# ============================================================================
# OS junk
# ============================================================================
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
*.swp
*~

# ============================================================================
# IDE / editor
# ============================================================================
.idea/
.vscode/
*.sublime-*

# ============================================================================
# Optional: generated outputs
# If you regenerate a lot and don't want the .txt/.sub templates in git,
# uncomment the next line. Most people keep them because they are useful
# skeletons with JESSE's comments baked in.
# fcc_research/generated/

# ============================================================================
# Notes from JESSE
# ============================================================================
# - The car_hacks_au/ folders are documented as "for YOUR captures only".
#   The .gitignore above makes that safer for public forks.
# - If you're contributing a verified capture back to the repo, you will
#   usually need to force-add it or temporarily comment the *.sub rules.
# - Personal notes files, ProtoPirate exports, URH sessions etc. are your
#   business — feel free to add more ignore patterns for your workflow.
#
# Deadset: better to have too many ignores than to leak your own fob timings
# into a public git history by accident.
#
# She'll be right.
# — JESSE

